      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification report — hemolysis predictions",
      "description": "Report documenting Latin hypercube sampling (n=2000) over uncertain input parameters including viscosity (±5%), inlet velocity profile shape, red blood cell fragility index, and power-law exponent. 95th-percentile NIH outputs tabulated per operating point. Sobol sensitivity indices computed to identify dominant uncertainty contributors.",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jbiomech.2021.110478"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/grid-convergence-report",
